HEADWORD: Champ
<hw>Champ</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To bite or chew
impatiently.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They began . . . irefully to <qex>champ</qex> upon the bit.</q>
<rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

